headline: Nike Layoffs And Data Breach Probe Test Turnaround And Valuation
summary: Nike is cutting 775 jobs at its US distribution centers as it speeds up the use of automation in its logistics network. The company is separately investigating a potential ransomware related data breach involving a large volume of internal data. Both developments come as NIKE (NYSE:NKE) continues an operational turnaround, with new risks around data security and customer privacy under review.
